Ruins\c[0]
Thief Nora: There's a goddess statue here too!

Mage Relm: It looks just like the ancient ruins and the
Lachio ruins. I wonder if it was created by the same people
for the same purpose.

Bard: That's a good analysis, but it might be a little
different.

Priestess Sophia: From a place with nothing... Haa, I have
the confidence to never be surprised by whatever happens in
the future.

Bard: The Kingdom of Basileia created similar training
grounds so that humans can fight against demons.
Bard: I think the ruins you all visited are part of it.
Mage Relm: Melos-san's prediction was almost spot on, huh...

Bard: This place was created by the goddess Actina as a
training ground for heroes.

Bard: Well, we didn't need to use it since we didn't have to
train.

Mage Relm: So... are you saying that the trials created by
the goddess are still untouched here!?

Bard: Haha, that's right. I don't know the details either,
but...
Bard: I think something useful has been prepared.

Bard: That's the end of the explanation. Well, whether you
go or not is up to your judgment.
Mage Relm: Everyone, have you all made your decision...?

Thief Nora: Hey, that's not fair! You're asking in a way
that I can't refuse!

Priestess Sophia: Will we be able to pass the trials of the
goddess Actina?
Do you want to enter the boss area?
Clea (Let's prepare first before doing that)
Clea: As expected, it's the same as the other places.
Clea: Let's take on the challenge.
Clea: We've cleared the first gate... I see.
Clea: Let's continue forward aiming for the deepest part.
